storyofscottis01birc |volume=Vol. 1, The Royal Seals of Scotland |publisher=Eneas Mackay |location=Stirling |via=[[Internet Archive]] |ref=B9 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Boardman |first=S |authorlink=Steve Boardman (historian) |year=2000 |chapter=The Tale of Leper John and the Campbell Acquisition of Lorn |editor1-last=Cowan |editor1-first=EJ |editor1-link=Edward J. Cowan |editor2-last=McDonald |editor2-first=RA |title=Alba: Celtic Scotland in the Middle Ages |publisher=Tuckwell Press |location=East Linton |pages=219\u2013247 |isbn=1-86232-151-5 |ref=B1 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Boardman |first=S |authorlink=Steve Boardman (historian) |chapter=Kingship: 4. Bruce Dynasty |year=2001a |editor-last=Lynch |editor-first=M |editor-link=Michael Lynch (historian) |title=The Oxford Companion to Scottish History |series=[[Oxford Companions]] |publisher=[[Oxford University Press]] |location=Oxford |pages=362\u2013363 |isbn=0-19-211696-7 |ref=B10 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Boardman |first=S |authorlink=Steve Boardman (historian) |chapter=Kingship: 5. Stewart Dynasty, to James V |year=2001b |editor-last=Lynch |editor-first=M |editor-link=Michael Lynch (historian) |title=The Oxford Companion to Scottish History |series=Oxford Companions |publisher=[[Oxford University Press]] |location=Oxford |pages=363\u2013366 |isbn=0-19-211696-7 |ref=B11 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Boardman |first=S |authorlink=Steve Boardman (historian) |year=2006 |title=The Campbells, 1250\u20131513 |publisher=John Donald |location=Edinburgh |isbn=978-0-85976-631-9 |ref=B14 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Boardman |first=S |author-link=Steve Boardman (historian) |year=2007 |chapter=The Gaelic World and the Early Stewart Court |chapter-url=http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/scottishstudies/ebooks/chap%203%20boardman.pdf |editor1-last=Broun |editor1-first=D |editor1-link=Dauvit Broun |editor2-last=MacGregor |editor2-first=M |title=M\u00ecorun M\u00f2r nan Gall, 'The Great Ill-Will of the Lowlander'? Lowland Perceptions of the Highlands, Medieval 